The paper proposes a novel discriminant analysis algorithm for feature extraction using mutual information. This involves working with high-dimensional data and finding an efficient method for feature extraction. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed method using UCI databases. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with algorithms for high-dimensional data and feature extraction. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as they also deal with similar topics. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories as they involve working with high-dimensional data and feature extraction.
